# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Credentials for the login Cucumber suite.
#
# Local dev:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env` (also gitignored — see .gitignore).
#   2. Fill in real values for each key.
#   3. Run the suite normally. CredentialsStore reads env vars first and falls
#      back to .env, so either source works.
#
# CI:
#   GitHub Actions injects each LOGIN_* key as an env var sourced from repo
#   Secrets — see .github/workflows/{ios,android}-tests.yml.
#
# What's in here vs. what isn't:
#   Only the valid user goes through this file. The negative-test aliases
#   ("the unknown user", "the wrong-password user", "the empty-username user")
#   are synthetic test fixtures and live as inline literals in
#   CredentialsStore — they aren't real credentials and don't need hiding.
#
# Rules:
#   - Missing key  ->  IllegalStateException at first lookup (fatal).
#   - Empty value  ->  allowed.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# For the bundled TheApp (https://github.com/cloudgrey-io/the-app), the
# publicly-documented demo credentials are:
#   LOGIN_VALID_USER=alice
#   LOGIN_VALID_PASSWORD=mypassword
# Drop those values into your local `.env` to run the suite as-is. If you
# point the framework at a different app, supply that app's real credentials
# (or, in CI, configure them as GitHub Secrets) and never commit them.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

LOGIN_VALID_USER=
LOGIN_VALID_PASSWORD=
